- Created AWS instance with pre-generate key pair
- Logged in using ssh ubuntu@ec2-13-232-83-155.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com
- Once in, sudo apt update && sudo snap install docker && sudo apt install docker-compose &&
docker-machine create default && sudo service docker start && sudo usermod -a -G docker ubuntu
- Follow Jitsi installation guide from https://jitsi.github.io/handbook/docs/devops-guide/devops-guide-docker
- Changed docker-compose.yml port mapping to 80:80 and 443:443
- Jitsi should now be publicly accessible on https://ec2-13-232-83-155.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com/

- Follow Calla instructions from https://github.com/saurabhagas/Calla/tree/master/Calla
- cd ~/.jitsi-meet-cfg && sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu .jitsi-meet-cfg
- Open http://ec2-13-232-83-155.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com:8080/Calla-Site/wwwroot/basic/ in browser
- Set up SSL in nginx using https://codingwithmanny.medium.com/configure-self-signed-ssl-for-nginx-docker-from-a-scratch-7c2bcd5478c6.
Use EC2 instance's hostname to generate SSL keys. Change /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf file to make nginx use these keys.
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -subj "/C=CA/ST=QC/O=Company, Inc./CN=ec2-35-154-21-100.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com" -addext "subjectAltName=DNS:ec2-35-154-21-100.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com" -newkey rsa:2048 -keyout /etc/ssl/private/nginx-selfsigned.key -out /etc/ssl/certs/nginx-selfsigned.crt;